## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

### ❌ DON'T DO THIS

```javascript
// 1. Business logic in handlers
bot.command('article', async (ctx) => {
  const html = await axios.get(url); // ❌ Should be in service
  const $ = cheerio.load(html);
  const section = $('h2').text(); // ❌ Parsing logic in handler
});

// 2. Hardcoded values
const timeout = 10000; // ❌ Should be in config/constants.js

// 3. Unvalidated URLs
await axios.get(userUrl); // ❌ SECURITY VULNERABILITY

// 4. Missing error handling
const result = await riskyOperation(); // ❌ No try-catch

// 5. Exposing errors
catch (err) {
  await ctx.reply(err.stack); // ❌ Never expose stack traces
}

// 6. Missing input validation
const number = parseInt(args[1]); // ❌ No validation
await service.process(number);
```

### ✅ DO THIS INSTEAD

```javascript
// Delegate to services with full error handling
bot.command("article", rateLimitMiddleware(), async (ctx) => {
  try {
    const number = parseInt(args[1], 10);
    if (isNaN(number) || number < 1) {
      await ctx.reply("❌ Invalid article number");
      return;
    }

    const text = await articleService.getArticle(number);
    await ctx.reply(text);
  } catch (err) {
    console.error("Error:", err);
    await ctx.reply("❌ Failed to fetch article");
  }
});
```

## Code Review Checklist

Before suggesting code, verify:

- [ ] Follows project architecture (handlers thin, logic in services)
- [ ] Module placement correct (services/, handlers/, middleware/, etc.)
- [ ] Input validation present
- [ ] URL validation for external URLs
- [ ] Rate limiting applied (if user-facing command)
- [ ] Authorization checked (if admin command)
- [ ] Error handling with try-catch
- [ ] User-friendly error messages (no stack traces)
- [ ] No hardcoded values (use constants)
- [ ] JSDoc comments for functions
- [ ] Async/await used consistently
- [ ] No floating promises
- [ ] Follows naming conventions
- [ ] No security vulnerabilities
- [ ] **Relevant skill file consulted** (if applicable)

## Development Workflow

### Setup

```bash
bun install
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with BOT_TOKEN and TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID
bun scripts/test-article.js 260  # Test scraping
bun dev  # Start with hot reload
```

### Testing

```bash
# Test specific article
bun scripts/test-article.js <number>

# Development mode
bun dev

# Production mode
bun prod
```

## Environment Variables

### Required

```bash
BOT_TOKEN=your_telegram_bot_token_from_botfather
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=your_chat_id_where_bot_sends_messages
```

### Optional

```bash
ALLOWED_USER_IDS=comma,separated,user,ids,for,admin,commands
NODE_ENV=production  # Set to "production" in production
